after their initial login.  Students are given a space quota of 1 GB and print quota of 600 pages per semester.  Accounts can be accessed by logging on to the lab workstations or remote servers, allowing students the flexibility to complete their course work from the lab, home or work.       Computing Resources   The instructional computing facility offers the following equipment:  Department workstations   52 Linux machines (CentOS7)  1 printer  4 LCD monitors for student collaboration   Department remote servers   cs.uic.edu  cs.uic.edu  cs.uic.edu        Location and hours   Second floor of SEL (room 2254).  Monday – Thursday (during the fall and spring semesters): 8 a.m. to 11 p.m.  Friday (during the fall and spring semesters): 8 a.m. to 9 p.m.  In case of problems or errors, please contact the lab consultant on duty or email support@cs.uic.edu .                    UIC Logo         College of  Engineering           Footer Menu    Undergraduate Resources    Graduate Resources    Faculty Resources    ABET Accreditation         Contact   For CS student and faculty inquiries, contact:  851 S. Morgan St., 11th Floor SEO, Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996-3422  cs-info@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    LinkedIn    Twitter    Instagram    YouTube             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 